445
00:30:46,803 --> 00:30:47,887
вЂЄYou were in here?

446
00:30:49,848 --> 00:30:53,810
вЂЄMan, all I did was kick in a door,
вЂЄand now my leg hurts.

447
00:30:53,893 --> 00:30:54,853
вЂЄGosh, it hurts.

448
00:30:58,857 --> 00:31:01,526
вЂЄWhat are you looking at?

449
00:31:01,609 --> 00:31:03,528
вЂЄWhy aren't you greeting your senior?

450
00:31:03,611 --> 00:31:04,821
вЂЄYou crazy littleвЂ¦

451
00:31:05,905 --> 00:31:07,282
вЂЄDon't you know how to knock?

452
00:31:07,365 --> 00:31:10,326
вЂЄWhy did you kick my office door
вЂЄlike a donkey?

453
00:31:10,410 --> 00:31:12,036
вЂЄIs this my doorknob?

454
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:13,913
вЂЄI did knock, 12 times.

455
00:31:13,997 --> 00:31:15,540
вЂЄYou didn't hear me because of your game.

456
00:31:15,623 --> 00:31:18,626
вЂЄA Taekwondo master like you
вЂЄshould have better manners.

457
00:31:19,127 --> 00:31:21,087
вЂЄJeez!

458
00:31:22,213 --> 00:31:23,631
вЂЄEverybody, fall in.

459
00:31:25,508 --> 00:31:27,010
вЂЄWhat are you, a kid?

460
00:31:30,471 --> 00:31:32,181
вЂЄThis is an important battle, okay?

461
00:31:32,265 --> 00:31:33,558
вЂЄYou want to end up like that door?

462
00:31:33,641 --> 00:31:35,727
вЂЄKim should be getting off work now.

463
00:31:35,810 --> 00:31:37,520
вЂЄHurry up and go before I smash that.

464
00:31:37,604 --> 00:31:39,606
вЂЄWhat does him getting off work
вЂЄhave to do with me?

465
00:31:40,815 --> 00:31:43,776
вЂЄToday's the one day out of the year
вЂЄwe get together!

466
00:31:45,236 --> 00:31:46,112
вЂЄThat's today?

467
00:31:49,866 --> 00:31:51,159
вЂЄSeriously, it's today?

468
00:31:52,285 --> 00:31:53,369
вЂЄOh man.

469
00:31:54,495 --> 00:31:55,830
вЂЄI must be getting old.

470
00:31:55,914 --> 00:31:57,373
вЂЄIt slipped my mind.

471
00:31:57,457 --> 00:32:00,418
вЂЄCome on. Let's go see how much he's aged.

472
00:32:01,210 --> 00:32:02,420
вЂЄGoodness gracious.

473
00:32:02,503 --> 00:32:04,756
вЂЄHey, what are you going to do about this?

474
00:32:05,256 --> 00:32:06,215
вЂЄHuh?

475
00:32:07,008 --> 00:32:07,967
вЂЄJust stick it back in.

476
00:32:08,676 --> 00:32:10,553
вЂЄ"Just stick it back in"?

477
00:32:12,305 --> 00:32:13,473
вЂЄI can just stick it in?

478
00:32:18,144 --> 00:32:20,647
вЂЄAll right.

479
00:32:20,730 --> 00:32:22,982
вЂЄIt's nice and cold. Drink up.

480
00:32:23,066 --> 00:32:24,317
вЂЄYeah, give me soju.

481
00:32:24,901 --> 00:32:25,985
вЂЄRight here.

482
00:32:27,695 --> 00:32:31,407
вЂЄThat white Taekwondo uniform
вЂЄis getting on my damn nerves.

483
00:32:31,491 --> 00:32:33,201
вЂЄIt's embarrassing.
вЂЄGo sit over there alone.

484
00:32:33,284 --> 00:32:35,453
вЂЄI came straight here
вЂЄafter dropping the kids off.

485
00:32:35,536 --> 00:32:37,330
вЂЄDon't flip the meat yet.

486
00:32:39,374 --> 00:32:41,250
вЂЄYou're one to talk.
вЂЄTake a look at yourself.

487
00:32:41,334 --> 00:32:43,086
вЂЄAre you going on a mission after you eat?

488
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:45,880
вЂЄHey, what's wrong with this?
вЂЄYou embarrassed?

489
00:32:45,964 --> 00:32:48,341
вЂЄWho looks more ridiculous
вЂЄbetween the two of us?

490
00:32:48,424 --> 00:32:51,219
вЂЄI just need to take off my jacket.

491
00:32:51,302 --> 00:32:52,553
вЂЄWow.

492
00:32:52,637 --> 00:32:54,055
вЂЄLook, it's Da-bin. Say hello.

493
00:32:54,138 --> 00:32:55,807
вЂЄ-Hi.
вЂЄ-Hi.

494
00:32:57,225 --> 00:32:59,143
вЂЄI wear this because I miss my daughter.

495
00:32:59,227 --> 00:33:01,562
вЂЄShe's out and about all the time,

496
00:33:01,646 --> 00:33:03,106
вЂЄso I never get to see her.

497
00:33:03,690 --> 00:33:05,817
вЂЄBut if I look in the mirror, I can say,

498
00:33:05,900 --> 00:33:08,695
вЂЄ"Hey, look who it is.
вЂЄIt's my daughter, Da-bin!"

499
00:33:08,778 --> 00:33:10,488
вЂЄ"It's me, your dad. Good to see you."

500
00:33:10,571 --> 00:33:12,198
вЂЄ"So, are you coming home today?"

501
00:33:12,281 --> 00:33:14,492
вЂЄDa-bin seems embarrassed by you.

502
00:33:14,575 --> 00:33:15,785
вЂЄShe can't hold her head up.

503
00:33:15,868 --> 00:33:17,453
вЂЄLet me help her with that.

504
00:33:17,537 --> 00:33:18,371
вЂЄHey.

505
00:33:18,454 --> 00:33:19,914
вЂЄYou're reminding me of the door.

506
00:33:19,998 --> 00:33:21,582
вЂЄDo you need me
вЂЄto put you in your place again?

507
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:29,716
вЂЄThe meat is burning.

508
00:33:32,301 --> 00:33:33,302
вЂЄYou're ridiculous.

509
00:33:37,056 --> 00:33:40,226
вЂЄNo answer or anything. He just walks by.

510
00:33:40,309 --> 00:33:41,686
вЂЄ-Seriously?
вЂЄ-Here.

511
00:33:41,769 --> 00:33:43,980
вЂЄ-All right, all right.
вЂЄ-Let's drink.

512
00:33:44,063 --> 00:33:45,273
вЂЄ-Cheers.
вЂЄ-Cheers.

513
00:33:47,942 --> 00:33:52,321
вЂЄI wonder who Tae-hun takes after
вЂЄto be so rude.

514
00:33:52,405 --> 00:33:53,364
вЂЄ-You.
вЂЄ-You.

515
00:33:53,448 --> 00:33:55,366
вЂЄRight, I'm rude.

516
00:34:02,290 --> 00:34:05,168
вЂЄThese drinks taste bittersweet tonight.

517
00:34:05,251 --> 00:34:06,919
вЂЄBut you know what?

518
00:34:07,003 --> 00:34:08,880
вЂЄRaising Da-bin is what keeps me going.

519
00:34:08,963 --> 00:34:12,175
вЂЄYou know, I may not be as strong

520
00:34:12,258 --> 00:34:14,260
вЂЄor as successful as before,

521
00:34:14,343 --> 00:34:15,678
вЂЄbut I like my life right now.

522
00:34:15,762 --> 00:34:17,513
вЂЄ-You punk.
вЂЄ-But I have to say,

523
00:34:17,597 --> 00:34:19,307
вЂЄDa-bin grew up too quickly.

524
00:34:19,390 --> 00:34:22,101
вЂЄShe was such a cute little baby,

525
00:34:22,185 --> 00:34:24,479
вЂЄbut now that she's in high school,
вЂЄshe refuses to listen to me.

526
00:34:24,562 --> 00:34:25,980
вЂЄSoon enough, she'll meet someone

527
00:34:26,898 --> 00:34:28,066
вЂЄand get married, right?

528
00:34:28,691 --> 00:34:31,194
вЂЄAnd we'll grow further apart, right?

529
00:34:32,779 --> 00:34:33,613
вЂЄThat justвЂ¦

530
00:34:34,447 --> 00:34:37,158
вЂЄJust thinking about it breaks my heart.

531
00:34:38,534 --> 00:34:39,535
вЂЄDa-bin.

532
00:34:40,328 --> 00:34:42,288
вЂЄPlease don't leave me.

533
00:34:42,371 --> 00:34:45,625
вЂЄYou're not a fool for your daughter.
вЂЄYou're just a fool.

534
00:34:46,918 --> 00:34:47,752
вЂЄI have to go.

535
00:34:47,835 --> 00:34:49,462
вЂЄ-Already?
вЂЄ-Already?

536
00:34:49,545 --> 00:34:50,630
вЂЄMin-ji's alone.

537
00:34:50,713 --> 00:34:54,842
вЂЄHey, she might not like it
вЂЄif you always rush home early.

538
00:34:55,593 --> 00:34:57,053
вЂЄDon't drink too much and go home.

539
00:34:57,136 --> 00:34:58,846
вЂЄ-What's this?
вЂЄ-Give it to your kids.

540
00:34:58,930 --> 00:35:00,807
вЂЄ-Jeez, come on.
вЂЄ-You shouldn't have.

541
00:35:00,890 --> 00:35:02,391
вЂЄ-Hey, hold on.
вЂЄ-Wait a minute.

542
00:35:02,475 --> 00:35:04,977
вЂЄJust sit down for a bit. Two more minutes.

543
00:35:05,061 --> 00:35:06,479
вЂЄDon't be so cold.

544
00:35:09,190 --> 00:35:10,900
вЂЄYou didn't have to.

545
00:35:13,528 --> 00:35:16,239
вЂЄHey, Da-bin.
вЂЄYour uncle gave you pocket money.

546
00:35:16,322 --> 00:35:18,407
вЂЄ-Listen, Kim.
вЂЄ-You should thank him.

547
00:35:18,491 --> 00:35:21,452
вЂЄLet's see each other more often, okay?

548
00:35:21,536 --> 00:35:24,288
вЂЄSeriously, once a year? That's ridiculous.

549
00:35:24,372 --> 00:35:26,707
вЂЄIf we meet once a year,

550
00:35:26,791 --> 00:35:30,378
вЂЄ-that's only 35 more times at best.
вЂЄ-That's true.

551
00:35:30,461 --> 00:35:34,841
вЂЄI understand the decision you made
вЂЄafter your wife passed away,

552
00:35:34,924 --> 00:35:36,551
вЂЄbut you need to live your own life too.

553
00:35:36,634 --> 00:35:40,263
вЂЄWhen will you stop making your daughter
вЂЄthe sole focus of your life?

554
00:35:40,346 --> 00:35:42,515
вЂЄ-Min-ji's grown up now.
вЂЄ-He's right.

555
00:35:42,598 --> 00:35:44,308
вЂЄShe'll have a boyfriend soon too.

556
00:35:44,392 --> 00:35:45,309
вЂЄShe's still a kid.

557
00:35:45,393 --> 00:35:48,396
вЂЄThe more you hover over your kids,

558
00:35:48,479 --> 00:35:50,898
вЂЄthe more suffocated they'll feel.

559
00:35:50,982 --> 00:35:53,234
вЂЄStop being so damn annoying!

560
00:35:54,402 --> 00:35:57,196
вЂЄCome on, can't we have a quiet meal?

561
00:35:57,280 --> 00:35:59,157
вЂЄHe's pissing me off!

562
00:35:59,240 --> 00:36:01,492
вЂЄ-Can you just put out your cigarette?
вЂЄ-Why?

563
00:36:01,576 --> 00:36:03,578
вЂЄThis is a terrace!
вЂЄWhy do I have to put it out?

564
00:36:03,661 --> 00:36:05,746
вЂЄThere are other customers here.

565
00:36:05,830 --> 00:36:08,166
вЂЄWhat other customers? Who?

566
00:36:08,916 --> 00:36:10,001
вЂЄWho?

567
00:36:10,543 --> 00:36:11,752
вЂЄWho?

568
00:36:14,630 --> 00:36:16,048
вЂЄ-Stop staring.
вЂЄ-What are you looking at?

569
00:36:16,132 --> 00:36:17,842
вЂЄWhat? You pissed off?

570
00:36:21,470 --> 00:36:23,097
вЂЄHe must be really pissed.

571
00:36:25,224 --> 00:36:26,642
вЂЄWhat?

572
00:36:27,518 --> 00:36:29,645
вЂЄDon't. This has nothing to do with us.

573
00:36:29,729 --> 00:36:32,481
вЂЄWe're middle-aged men
вЂЄwho tolerate injustice.

574
00:36:32,565 --> 00:36:33,774
вЂЄWe're no longer young.

575
00:36:33,858 --> 00:36:35,818
вЂЄWe're just middle-aged men with glasses.

576
00:36:35,902 --> 00:36:36,903
вЂЄRight?

577
00:36:36,986 --> 00:36:39,238
вЂЄWe already paid, so let's go.

578
00:36:39,322 --> 00:36:40,281
вЂЄCome on.

579
00:36:40,364 --> 00:36:41,365
вЂЄGet up.

580
00:36:42,617 --> 00:36:44,118
вЂЄHey, grunt! Where are you going?

581
00:36:44,202 --> 00:36:45,536
вЂЄ-Enough already.
вЂЄ-Let go of me.

582
00:36:45,620 --> 00:36:47,163
вЂЄYou off to scrub the slop bucket?

583
00:36:48,122 --> 00:36:50,124
вЂЄJin-cheol. You remember, right?

584
00:36:50,208 --> 00:36:51,042
вЂЄRight.

585
00:36:51,959 --> 00:36:54,337
вЂЄWe're just middle-aged men with glasses.

586
00:36:56,088 --> 00:36:57,590
вЂЄWhat? You scared?

587
00:37:00,593 --> 00:37:03,846
вЂЄYou were glaring at me earlier.

588
00:37:03,930 --> 00:37:05,473
вЂЄGet over here, you asshole!

589
00:37:05,556 --> 00:37:07,600
вЂЄHey, grunt. Why don't you do some drills?

590
00:37:07,683 --> 00:37:08,768
вЂЄCome on, give me 20 reps.

591
00:37:09,894 --> 00:37:11,103
вЂЄOne, two!

592
00:37:11,187 --> 00:37:12,313
вЂЄWhat's that?

593
00:37:12,396 --> 00:37:14,357
вЂЄThis is embarrassing. Who's this?

594
00:37:14,440 --> 00:37:15,691
вЂЄShe's pretty!

595
00:37:16,192 --> 00:37:17,401
вЂЄHow cute.

596
00:37:18,653 --> 00:37:20,321
вЂЄWhy don't you introduce me to her?

597
00:37:21,155 --> 00:37:22,448
вЂЄI'll treat her really well.

598
00:37:22,949 --> 00:37:24,951
<i>вЂЄRock and roll!</i>

599
00:37:29,455 --> 00:37:30,289
вЂЄJin-cheol.

600
00:37:38,214 --> 00:37:39,215
вЂЄWhat the hell?

601
00:37:39,882 --> 00:37:41,634
вЂЄYou fat pig!

602
00:37:43,678 --> 00:37:45,137
вЂЄHey, pig, get up.

603
00:37:45,846 --> 00:37:47,098
вЂЄLet me borrow your bag.

604
00:37:51,560 --> 00:37:53,521
вЂЄKim, shouldn't we stop him?

605
00:37:54,689 --> 00:37:55,898
вЂЄWhere did he go?

606
00:37:58,859 --> 00:38:02,071
вЂЄDid you see a tall guy with glasses
вЂЄin a depressing black suit?

607
00:38:03,281 --> 00:38:04,490
вЂЄA tall guy.

608
00:38:07,243 --> 00:38:08,119
вЂЄHey, KimвЂ¦

609
00:38:09,787 --> 00:38:10,913
вЂЄFine, just go.

610
00:38:13,874 --> 00:38:15,126
вЂЄIs this the police?

611
00:38:15,209 --> 00:38:17,169
вЂЄThere's a fight going on right now.

612
00:38:17,253 --> 00:38:19,422
вЂЄYes, a serious fight. Someone might die.

613
00:38:19,505 --> 00:38:20,840
вЂЄPlease hurry!

614
00:38:25,428 --> 00:38:28,514
вЂЄNo, no. You're dead if you use that.
вЂЄNo, don't do that.

615
00:38:36,188 --> 00:38:38,566
вЂЄHe should run. Is he frozen or something?

616
00:39:04,842 --> 00:39:06,093
вЂЄStop.

617
00:39:06,719 --> 00:39:07,553
вЂЄStop!

618
00:39:14,185 --> 00:39:17,063
вЂЄOfficer, shoot something!

619
00:39:17,146 --> 00:39:19,190
вЂЄ-Shoot your gun!
вЂЄ-Gun?

620
00:39:19,273 --> 00:39:21,942
вЂЄShoot something! Anything! Hurry!

621
00:39:24,070 --> 00:39:25,279
вЂЄHurry!

622
00:39:41,670 --> 00:39:43,589
вЂЄWhose jacket is this? "Kim Nam-hoon"?

623
00:39:43,672 --> 00:39:45,341
вЂЄ-What are you doing?
вЂЄ-Who's Kim Nam-hoon?

624
00:39:45,424 --> 00:39:46,967
вЂЄI don't know.

625
00:39:47,051 --> 00:39:49,095
вЂЄWhat's the matter with you?

626
00:39:49,762 --> 00:39:50,971
вЂЄHave a good day.

627
00:39:54,892 --> 00:39:57,019
вЂЄMin-ji's grown up now.

628
00:39:57,103 --> 00:39:58,646
вЂЄHe's right.
вЂЄShe'll have a boyfriend soon too.

629
00:39:59,230 --> 00:40:01,315
вЂЄDoes she have a boyfriend?

630
00:40:12,993 --> 00:40:14,036
вЂЄHey.

631
00:40:14,829 --> 00:40:16,872
вЂЄDo you know where Kim Nam-hoon is?

632
00:40:19,208 --> 00:40:20,042
вЂЄI'm not sure.

633
00:40:26,048 --> 00:40:27,216
вЂЄI need to give this back.

634
00:40:35,724 --> 00:40:38,477
вЂЄ-You could've left it on my desk.
вЂЄ-What?

635
00:40:38,561 --> 00:40:39,979
вЂЄYou were looking for me, right?

636
00:40:40,062 --> 00:40:42,440
вЂЄOh, I just wanted to thank you.

637
00:40:43,816 --> 00:40:45,276
вЂЄ-That's it?
вЂЄ-WellвЂ¦

638
00:40:45,359 --> 00:40:46,694
вЂЄI can give you this.

639
00:40:50,948 --> 00:40:52,283
вЂЄReally? Strawberry milk?

640
00:40:52,366 --> 00:40:53,534
вЂЄWhat am I, a kid?

641
00:41:09,842 --> 00:41:11,177
вЂЄYou're the one who liked my post, right?

642
00:41:11,260 --> 00:41:12,094
вЂЄWhat?

643
00:41:13,220 --> 00:41:14,305
вЂЄI'm not on social media.

644
00:41:15,723 --> 00:41:16,932
вЂЄOh, yeah?

645
00:41:30,362 --> 00:41:31,489
<i>вЂЄThen what's this?</i>

646
00:41:31,572 --> 00:41:32,656
вЂЄKIM NAM-HOON

647
00:41:35,242 --> 00:41:36,327
вЂЄI can DM you, right?

648
00:41:37,703 --> 00:41:38,537
вЂЄYeah.

649
00:41:39,163 --> 00:41:40,623
вЂЄNever mind. You should DM me first.

650
00:41:40,706 --> 00:41:41,540
вЂЄHey.

651
00:41:41,624 --> 00:41:44,126
вЂЄBut you have to DM me back.

652
00:41:44,210 --> 00:41:45,252
вЂЄI'll think about it.

653
00:41:45,336 --> 00:41:47,505
вЂЄ-Why? What's there to think about?
вЂЄ-What?

654
00:41:47,588 --> 00:41:49,256
вЂЄWhy can't I think about it?

655
00:41:49,340 --> 00:41:52,092
вЂЄYou can't do that.
вЂЄYou told me to DM you first.

656
00:42:07,525 --> 00:42:08,901
вЂЄCome out. Hye-ri wants to see you.

657
00:42:10,569 --> 00:42:11,487
вЂЄGet up.

658
00:42:28,921 --> 00:42:29,964
вЂЄYou know why I hit you, right?

659
00:42:31,173 --> 00:42:33,634
вЂЄHye-ri asked you a question. Answer her.

660
00:42:37,888 --> 00:42:38,931
вЂЄYou still don't know?

661
00:42:39,014 --> 00:42:42,601
вЂЄYou hit on Hye-ri's boyfriend,
вЂЄyou sly bitch.

662
00:42:42,685 --> 00:42:43,602
вЂЄI never did that.

663
00:42:43,686 --> 00:42:45,729
вЂЄAll I did was return his gym clothes.

664
00:42:46,814 --> 00:42:50,651
вЂЄWhy did you borrow them
вЂЄin the first place?

665
00:42:51,443 --> 00:42:52,736
вЂЄWho do you think you are?

666
00:42:52,820 --> 00:42:55,281
вЂЄWhy didn't you wear
вЂЄyour own goddamn gym clothes?

667
00:42:56,407 --> 00:42:58,200
вЂЄBecause you guys threw them in the trash.

668
00:43:01,287 --> 00:43:02,788
вЂЄDon't worry.

669
00:43:02,871 --> 00:43:04,373
вЂЄI have no reason to contact him.

670
00:43:05,040 --> 00:43:06,584
вЂЄI don't want anything to do with you.

671
00:43:16,844 --> 00:43:19,346
вЂЄHey, it seems like you're mistaken.

672
00:43:19,430 --> 00:43:23,350
вЂЄI'm not pissed
вЂЄbecause you tried to take my toy.

673
00:43:23,434 --> 00:43:25,561
вЂЄIt's because of your stench.

674
00:43:26,395 --> 00:43:28,314
вЂЄI'm pissed because it'll rub off on him.

675
00:43:29,231 --> 00:43:30,399
вЂЄShe has no idea.

676
00:43:31,400 --> 00:43:32,318
вЂЄGrab her.

677
00:43:36,155 --> 00:43:37,406
вЂЄGet up.

678
00:43:39,450 --> 00:43:42,411
вЂЄHow do I describe this smell?

679
00:43:52,880 --> 00:43:55,758
вЂЄIt's like a cheap suit

680
00:43:56,842 --> 00:43:59,678
вЂЄshoved in the back of a closetвЂ¦

681
00:44:00,888 --> 00:44:01,805
вЂЄOh, I know.

682
00:44:03,515 --> 00:44:04,933
вЂЄIt's the smell of a motherless child.

683
00:44:14,568 --> 00:44:15,694
вЂЄHey.

684
00:44:15,778 --> 00:44:18,656
вЂЄ-You think you know me?!
вЂЄ-You crazy bitch!

685
00:44:18,739 --> 00:44:20,324
вЂЄWho do you think you are?!

686
00:44:21,492 --> 00:44:22,701
вЂЄWho do you think you are? Huh?!

687
00:44:24,620 --> 00:44:26,955
вЂЄ-Hye-ri, are you okay?
вЂЄ-Who the hell do you think you are?!

688
00:44:31,752 --> 00:44:33,170
вЂЄHey!

689
00:44:33,253 --> 00:44:35,297
вЂЄYou think you know me so well?!

690
00:44:36,090 --> 00:44:38,008
вЂЄ-What the hell do you know?!
вЂЄ-Get off her!

691
00:44:38,092 --> 00:44:40,135
вЂЄ-Get off her already!
вЂЄ-Stop!

692
00:44:40,219 --> 00:44:43,180
<i>вЂЄIt wasn't just a fight.</i>
<i>вЂЄIt was an assault, Mr. Kim.</i>

693
00:44:43,263 --> 00:44:46,266
<i>вЂЄMin-ji just attacked her.</i>

694
00:44:46,350 --> 00:44:48,769
вЂЄI'll be right there.

695
00:44:48,852 --> 00:44:49,895
<i>вЂЄPlease hurry.</i>

696
00:44:50,521 --> 00:44:52,690
<i>вЂЄI'm about to lose my job.</i>

697
00:44:54,441 --> 00:44:55,818
<i>вЂЄWhy did it have to be Hye-ri?</i>

698
00:44:55,901 --> 00:45:00,280
<i>вЂЄThe victim's father is the chairman</i>
<i>вЂЄof Juhak Construction.</i>

699
00:45:00,364 --> 00:45:01,824
<i>вЂЄYou've heard of them, right?</i>

700
00:45:05,744 --> 00:45:07,162
вЂЄYou built this hotel as well,

701
00:45:07,704 --> 00:45:09,081
вЂЄdidn't you, Chairman Ju?

702
00:45:10,874 --> 00:45:11,708
вЂЄYes.

703
00:45:13,168 --> 00:45:15,462
вЂЄMy daughter had graduated
вЂЄfrom elementary school,

704
00:45:16,547 --> 00:45:17,881
вЂЄso it was about four years ago.

705
00:45:17,965 --> 00:45:21,009
вЂЄOh, you have a daughter.

706
00:45:21,093 --> 00:45:23,679
вЂЄShe must be pretty if she takes after you.

707
00:45:24,888 --> 00:45:25,722
вЂЄYou're too kind.

708
00:45:26,807 --> 00:45:31,061
вЂЄAnyway, this is the first time
вЂЄI've had a meeting in a spa.

709
00:45:31,145 --> 00:45:34,523
вЂЄThere's no need to watch what we say
вЂЄor hide anything here.

710
00:45:36,859 --> 00:45:37,860
вЂЄAll right, then.

711
00:45:38,819 --> 00:45:40,904
вЂЄLet me ask you point-blank.

712
00:45:40,988 --> 00:45:44,283
вЂЄWhat's in it for me
вЂЄif this redevelopment plan goes through?

713
00:45:44,366 --> 00:45:48,120
вЂЄIt'll provide a better living environment
вЂЄfor your constituents.

714
00:45:48,203 --> 00:45:49,371
вЂЄAnd?

715
00:45:50,372 --> 00:45:51,623
вЂЄIt'll create

716
00:45:53,292 --> 00:45:56,044
вЂЄa much more favorable environment
вЂЄfor your political fundraising.

717
00:45:57,838 --> 00:45:59,506
вЂЄTwice as much as last time.

718
00:46:06,054 --> 00:46:08,140
вЂЄAll right. Let's do this together.

719
00:46:08,223 --> 00:46:13,979
вЂЄThere must be something in the water.
вЂЄI feel refreshed to my very core.

720
00:46:15,063 --> 00:46:16,648
вЂЄI should get going now.

721
00:46:17,774 --> 00:46:18,817
вЂЄPlease take your time.

722
00:46:24,031 --> 00:46:25,491
вЂЄGoodness, Chairman Ju.

723
00:46:25,574 --> 00:46:27,242
вЂЄWhat happened to your body?

724
00:46:27,326 --> 00:46:29,536
вЂЄOh, it's not a pretty sight, is it?

725
00:46:31,497 --> 00:46:34,333
вЂЄI got some tattoos on a whim
вЂЄwhen I was younger,

726
00:46:35,584 --> 00:46:37,377
вЂЄbut I regretted them
вЂЄafter I started my business.

727
00:46:38,086 --> 00:46:39,421
вЂЄI was ashamed to show my daughter too.

728
00:46:40,756 --> 00:46:43,133
вЂЄSo I just burned them off myself
вЂЄwith a torch.

729
00:46:44,134 --> 00:46:46,053
вЂЄWith a torch?

730
00:46:46,678 --> 00:46:49,097
вЂЄWhy didn't you go to a hospital?

731
00:46:50,265 --> 00:46:53,602
вЂЄI guess it was a pledge
вЂЄnot to go back to my old life.

732
00:46:53,685 --> 00:46:57,689
вЂЄBut still, it must've been very painful.

733
00:47:00,359 --> 00:47:03,987
вЂЄIt was nothing compared to what I've done
вЂЄto make it this far.

734
00:47:04,571 --> 00:47:05,405
вЂЄIt was more painfulвЂ¦

735
00:47:07,699 --> 00:47:10,285
вЂЄfor those who didn't keep
вЂЄtheir promises with me

736
00:47:10,369 --> 00:47:12,120
вЂЄand disappeared as a result.

737
00:47:18,710 --> 00:47:20,337
вЂЄI'm counting on you, Assemblyman Sim.

738
00:47:20,420 --> 00:47:22,256
вЂЄRight, yes, of course.

739
00:47:28,512 --> 00:47:30,764
вЂЄSir, your wife is calling.

740
00:47:36,270 --> 00:47:38,397
вЂЄ-What is it?
<i>вЂЄ-Honey, something terrible happened.</i>

741
00:47:38,480 --> 00:47:39,690
<i>вЂЄHye-riвЂ¦</i>

742
00:47:39,773 --> 00:47:43,277
<i>вЂЄHye-ri was assaulted by someone at school!</i>

743
00:47:44,903 --> 00:47:45,821
вЂЄOkay.

744
00:47:50,325 --> 00:47:51,285
вЂЄLet's go to Hye-ri's school.

745
00:47:51,910 --> 00:47:53,161
вЂЄYes, sir.

746
00:48:18,437 --> 00:48:19,688
вЂЄYou can't go in.

747
00:48:21,815 --> 00:48:24,943
вЂЄThe chairman asked me to come, asshole.

748
00:48:25,027 --> 00:48:26,320
вЂЄHey, Nam.

749
00:48:27,112 --> 00:48:28,113
вЂЄWhat's the matter with them?

750
00:48:28,196 --> 00:48:29,156
вЂЄBe quiet.

751
00:48:30,157 --> 00:48:31,700
вЂЄThe chairman is inside.

752
00:48:34,995 --> 00:48:35,871
вЂЄYou told me to come.

753
00:48:35,954 --> 00:48:37,372
вЂЄSo I came.

754
00:48:37,456 --> 00:48:38,790
вЂЄThere's been a change of plans.

755
00:48:39,541 --> 00:48:40,792
вЂЄI'll get back to you.

756
00:48:45,047 --> 00:48:48,675
вЂЄAm I some lapdog
вЂЄyou can just order around?

757
00:48:56,183 --> 00:48:57,351
вЂЄI thought you knew already.

758
00:48:57,976 --> 00:48:58,977
вЂЄNo, I didn't.

759
00:49:05,275 --> 00:49:06,485
вЂЄI didn't know that.

760
00:49:08,570 --> 00:49:09,821
вЂЄThis lapdog is leaving.

761
00:49:11,823 --> 00:49:13,575
вЂЄGoddamn it.

762
00:49:16,536 --> 00:49:18,330
вЂЄWhen in the world is he arriving?

763
00:49:20,749 --> 00:49:22,000
вЂЄLet's go, Hye-ri.

764
00:49:22,084 --> 00:49:24,586
вЂЄHow dare he make us wait?

765
00:49:25,212 --> 00:49:26,129
вЂЄSit down.

766
00:49:27,172 --> 00:49:28,465
вЂЄWe should at least talk to him.

767
00:49:33,428 --> 00:49:36,306
вЂЄWhat took you so long?

768
00:49:43,897 --> 00:49:47,359
вЂЄHow on earth did you raise your child
вЂЄfor her to act this way?

769
00:49:48,318 --> 00:49:49,986
вЂЄJust look at my child!

770
00:49:50,070 --> 00:49:52,489
вЂЄHow can I send her to school now?

771
00:49:53,365 --> 00:49:54,491
вЂЄWhy won't you look at her?

772
00:49:55,075 --> 00:49:57,661
вЂЄTake a good look at her!

773
00:50:02,499 --> 00:50:03,542
вЂЄI'm sorry.

774
00:50:03,625 --> 00:50:06,128
вЂЄI've only heard about
вЂЄschool violence and bullies.

775
00:50:06,211 --> 00:50:10,215
вЂЄI had no idea Hye-ri was in the same class
вЂЄas someone like her!

776
00:50:10,298 --> 00:50:12,467
вЂЄDad, I didn't do anything wrong.

777
00:50:12,551 --> 00:50:14,428
вЂЄShe and her girls kept harassing me.

778
00:50:14,511 --> 00:50:16,763
вЂЄI took it for as long as I could
вЂЄbefore fighting back!

779
00:50:16,847 --> 00:50:17,764
вЂЄKim Min-ji.

780
00:50:19,558 --> 00:50:20,475
вЂЄBe quiet.

781
00:50:20,559 --> 00:50:22,769
вЂЄBut she hit me first!

782
00:50:22,853 --> 00:50:23,687
вЂЄDon't you believe me?

783
00:50:24,521 --> 00:50:25,355
вЂЄMin-ji.

784
00:50:27,733 --> 00:50:32,529
вЂЄMr. Kim, I think you should
вЂЄcome to an agreement with the victim.

785
00:50:32,612 --> 00:50:34,948
вЂЄNo, forget it.

786
00:50:35,031 --> 00:50:37,200
вЂЄI demand a disciplinary hearing,

787
00:50:37,284 --> 00:50:38,994
вЂЄand I want this on her record.

788
00:50:45,625 --> 00:50:47,169
вЂЄDad!

789
00:50:51,965 --> 00:50:53,592
вЂЄDon't you have any pride at all?

790
00:50:54,509 --> 00:50:55,343
вЂЄI'm sorry.

791
00:50:55,427 --> 00:50:57,220
вЂЄI've fallen short as a parent

792
00:50:58,054 --> 00:50:59,347
вЂЄsince I'm raising her alone.

793
00:51:00,015 --> 00:51:02,434
вЂЄAs a fellow parent raising a daughter,

794
00:51:02,517 --> 00:51:04,895
вЂЄI ask that you find it in your heart
вЂЄto forgive us.

795
00:51:07,230 --> 00:51:08,857
вЂЄI'll take responsibility as her father,

796
00:51:10,525 --> 00:51:11,526
вЂЄand have her transferred.

797
00:51:11,610 --> 00:51:12,694
вЂЄDad!

798
00:51:19,284 --> 00:51:21,203
вЂЄAs a fellow parent raising a daughter,
вЂЄyou say?

799
00:51:32,172 --> 00:51:33,006
вЂЄRight.

800
00:51:36,843 --> 00:51:38,470
вЂЄIt's not easy raising a daughter.

801
00:51:43,099 --> 00:51:44,184
вЂЄEspecially on your own.

802
00:51:46,895 --> 00:51:49,064
вЂЄIt must've been hard
вЂЄgrowing up without a mother.

803
00:51:50,315 --> 00:51:52,818
вЂЄIt's natural for kids to fight
вЂЄwhile growing up.

804
00:51:56,488 --> 00:51:57,864
вЂЄWe received an apology,

805
00:51:57,948 --> 00:51:59,866
вЂЄso let's settle this matter
вЂЄwith her transferring.

806
00:51:59,950 --> 00:52:00,784
вЂЄ-Dad!
вЂЄ-Honey!

807
00:52:00,867 --> 00:52:01,952
вЂЄWe'll leave it at this.

808
00:52:05,080 --> 00:52:05,914
вЂЄThank you.

809
00:52:17,801 --> 00:52:18,635
вЂЄMin-ji.

810
00:52:21,179 --> 00:52:22,389
вЂЄKim Min-ji.

811
00:52:23,348 --> 00:52:24,182
{\an8}вЂЄKIM NAM-HOON

812
00:52:37,571 --> 00:52:39,573
вЂЄWhat does her father do?

813
00:52:40,198 --> 00:52:43,702
вЂЄI believe he's an ordinary office worker.

814
00:52:43,785 --> 00:52:47,330
вЂЄThank you for your leniency, Chairman Ju.

815
00:52:48,039 --> 00:52:51,084
вЂЄThank you. This will never happen again.

816
00:52:53,461 --> 00:52:54,421
вЂЄOf course.

817
00:52:54,504 --> 00:52:56,548
вЂЄBecause if something like this
вЂЄhappens again,

818
00:52:58,008 --> 00:53:00,010
вЂЄthis school and all of you will disappear.

819
00:53:19,112 --> 00:53:19,988
вЂЄMin-ji.

820
00:53:22,073 --> 00:53:23,116
вЂЄAre you hungry?

821
00:53:24,242 --> 00:53:25,368
вЂЄShould we go eat?

822
00:53:27,662 --> 00:53:28,538
вЂЄMin-ji.

823
00:53:29,623 --> 00:53:30,624
вЂЄKim Min-ji.

824
00:53:34,920 --> 00:53:36,671
вЂЄWhy won't you believe me?

825
00:53:37,505 --> 00:53:38,882
вЂЄOf course, I believe you.

826
00:53:38,965 --> 00:53:41,134
вЂЄThen why do I have to transfer?

827
00:53:41,217 --> 00:53:42,886
вЂЄI didn't do anything wrong.

828
00:53:45,639 --> 00:53:47,891
вЂЄWhy did you have to grovel and kneel?

829
00:53:48,475 --> 00:53:50,518
вЂЄIs it because Hye-ri's dad
вЂЄis a powerful man?

830
00:53:51,269 --> 00:53:52,854
вЂЄI'm so ashamed.

831
00:53:53,855 --> 00:53:56,733
вЂЄI feel so angry, frustrated, and pathetic.

832
00:53:57,817 --> 00:53:59,569
вЂЄWhat have you done with your life?

833
00:54:01,196 --> 00:54:03,782
вЂЄHer dad's a rich chairman
вЂЄwith lots of connections,

834
00:54:04,574 --> 00:54:07,202
вЂЄbut why are you a lowly office worker?

835
00:54:08,411 --> 00:54:10,121
вЂЄWhy did you even have me?

836
00:54:11,998 --> 00:54:12,832
вЂЄMin-ji.

837
00:54:12,916 --> 00:54:13,959
вЂЄAs my dadвЂ¦

838
00:54:16,002 --> 00:54:17,170
вЂЄAs my dadвЂ¦

839
00:54:24,010 --> 00:54:26,680
вЂЄAs my dad, you mean the world to me.

840
00:54:27,639 --> 00:54:28,932
вЂЄI don't have a mom.

841
00:54:29,516 --> 00:54:31,101
вЂЄYou're all I have left,

842
00:54:32,310 --> 00:54:34,062
вЂЄbut if you're not on my sideвЂ¦

843
00:54:34,145 --> 00:54:36,147
вЂЄThey're the bad ones.

844
00:54:36,773 --> 00:54:39,651
вЂЄYou, of all people, should've believed me.

845
00:54:44,656 --> 00:54:45,573
вЂЄLet's go home.

846
00:54:45,657 --> 00:54:47,158
вЂЄI don't want to be with you.

847
00:54:47,742 --> 00:54:49,786
вЂЄI'm staying at Hye-ryeong's tonight,

848
00:54:49,869 --> 00:54:51,162
вЂЄso don't call me.

849
00:54:51,246 --> 00:54:52,747
вЂЄIf you do,

850
00:54:53,957 --> 00:54:55,709
вЂЄI'll run away from home.

851
00:54:57,669 --> 00:54:58,586
вЂЄMin-ji.

852
00:55:00,422 --> 00:55:02,007
вЂЄIt's your birthday tomorrow.

853
00:55:02,841 --> 00:55:03,675
вЂЄKim Min-ji!

854
00:55:11,307 --> 00:55:13,226
вЂЄI hate my birthday.

855
00:55:16,813 --> 00:55:18,481
вЂЄIt's the day Mom died.

856
00:55:52,057 --> 00:55:53,308
{\an8}вЂЄTHE LATE IM YU-JIN

857
00:56:15,038 --> 00:56:17,082
вЂЄThese flowers are my favorite.

858
00:56:17,665 --> 00:56:18,875
вЂЄThey're called honeysuckles.

859
00:56:19,375 --> 00:56:20,919
вЂЄThe meaning behind them is pretty too.

860
00:56:21,961 --> 00:56:23,088
вЂЄDo you know what it is?

861
00:56:23,671 --> 00:56:24,506
вЂЄWhat is it?

862
00:56:25,173 --> 00:56:26,007
вЂЄLove andвЂ¦

863
00:56:26,841 --> 00:56:27,801
вЂЄ-<i>вЂЄdevotion.</i>
вЂЄ-Devotion.

864
00:56:33,848 --> 00:56:36,392
вЂЄI'm sorry, Yu-jin.

865
00:57:40,582 --> 00:57:42,125
<i>вЂЄI have something to tell you.</i>

866
00:57:42,208 --> 00:57:44,169
<i>вЂЄI'll be at the back gate at school.</i>

867
00:57:44,252 --> 00:57:45,712
<i>вЂЄI'll wait until you get here.</i>

868
00:58:28,588 --> 00:58:31,925
вЂЄDAD

869
00:58:33,885 --> 00:58:36,846
<i>вЂЄThe person you are trying to reach</i>
<i>вЂЄis unavailable. You will be redirectedвЂ¦</i>

870
00:58:37,889 --> 00:58:39,599
<i>вЂЄI don't want to be with you.</i>

871
00:58:40,308 --> 00:58:42,435
вЂЄI'm staying at Hye-ryeong's tonight,

872
00:58:42,519 --> 00:58:43,811
вЂЄso don't call me.

873
00:58:45,188 --> 00:58:46,356
вЂЄIf you do,

874
00:58:47,565 --> 00:58:49,150
вЂЄI'll run away from home.

875
00:59:18,012 --> 00:59:21,766
<i>вЂЄThe phone you are calling is turned off.</i>
<i>вЂЄYou will be redirected to voicemail.</i>

876
00:59:36,155 --> 00:59:37,407
<i>вЂЄHello?</i>

877
00:59:37,490 --> 00:59:38,324
вЂЄHello?

878
00:59:39,117 --> 00:59:40,410
вЂЄIs this Kang Hye-ryeong?

879
00:59:40,493 --> 00:59:42,287
<i>вЂЄYes. Who is this?</i>

880
00:59:42,370 --> 00:59:44,330
вЂЄI'm Min-ji's dad.

881
00:59:44,414 --> 00:59:47,792
<i>вЂЄWhat? How did you know my number?</i>

882
00:59:49,335 --> 00:59:51,170
вЂЄMin-ji told me.

883
00:59:51,963 --> 00:59:54,632
вЂЄHye-ryeong, by any chance,

884
00:59:54,716 --> 00:59:56,509
вЂЄwere you with Min-ji last night?

885
00:59:56,593 --> 00:59:57,552
<i>вЂЄNo.</i>

886
00:59:59,512 --> 01:00:02,515
вЂЄThen have you heard from her at all?

887
01:00:02,599 --> 01:00:04,017
<i>вЂЄNo.</i>

888
01:00:04,100 --> 01:00:05,268
<i>вЂЄI'm hanging up now.</i>

889
01:00:33,630 --> 01:00:35,506
вЂЄHey, I'm Min-ji's dad.

890
01:00:36,090 --> 01:00:37,300
вЂЄHave you seen her?

891
01:00:40,720 --> 01:00:43,264
вЂЄNo, she hasn't come to school yet.

892
01:00:52,940 --> 01:00:54,108
вЂЄKim Nam-hoon?

893
01:00:55,109 --> 01:00:57,612
вЂЄDid you meet Min-ji yesterday?

894
01:00:59,280 --> 01:01:02,241
вЂЄI didn't send her that DM.

895
01:01:02,867 --> 01:01:04,327
вЂЄhey were these thugsвЂ¦

896
01:01:05,453 --> 01:01:07,455
<i>вЂЄI only heard something</i>
<i>вЂЄabout the back gate.</i>

897
01:01:08,373 --> 01:01:09,499
<i>вЂЄI'm sorry.</i>

898
01:01:10,416 --> 01:01:12,543
<i>вЂЄI couldn't do anything</i>

899
01:01:12,627 --> 01:01:14,003
<i>вЂЄbecause they took my phone.</i>

900
01:02:24,282 --> 01:02:27,827
<i>вЂЄHow on earth did you raise your child</i>
<i>вЂЄfor her to act this way?</i>

901
01:03:04,572 --> 01:03:06,491
вЂЄWe just have to act like
вЂЄwe don't know anything.

902
01:03:06,574 --> 01:03:08,618
вЂЄI told everyone to keep quiet,
вЂЄso don't worry.

903
01:03:08,701 --> 01:03:11,245
вЂЄ-But you never know.
вЂЄ-Just trust me.

904
01:03:11,329 --> 01:03:12,997
вЂЄYou know I'm not some low-life thug.

905
01:03:14,957 --> 01:03:16,501
вЂЄHey, it's all clean now.

906
01:03:17,084 --> 01:03:19,128
вЂЄSee? Even the weather is on our side.

907
01:03:20,588 --> 01:03:23,049
вЂЄIf someone reported it,
вЂЄthe cops would be here already.

908
01:03:23,132 --> 01:03:24,217
вЂЄNobody will find her.

909
01:03:24,300 --> 01:03:26,093
вЂЄAnd you said her dad's a loser, right?

910
01:03:27,094 --> 01:03:29,806
вЂЄ-Can I ask a question?
вЂЄ-Damn it, you scared me!

911
01:03:30,348 --> 01:03:32,809
вЂЄI'm Min-ji's dad.

912
01:03:33,935 --> 01:03:36,187
вЂЄWe don't know where she is,
вЂЄso just go on your way.

913
01:03:37,271 --> 01:03:39,440
вЂЄI never said I was looking for her.

914
01:03:44,612 --> 01:03:47,406
вЂЄThis is your hair tie, right?

915
01:03:47,490 --> 01:03:48,449
вЂЄIt was on the ground.

916
01:03:52,787 --> 01:03:56,457
вЂЄI said go on your way
вЂЄunless you want your ass kicked!

917
01:03:56,541 --> 01:03:58,793
вЂЄ-It's yours, right?
вЂЄ-Goddamn it.

918
01:04:08,845 --> 01:04:09,971
вЂЄLook at you.

919
01:04:11,180 --> 01:04:13,558
вЂЄ-You're dead meat.
вЂЄ-I'll ask you one last time.

920
01:04:14,976 --> 01:04:16,644
вЂЄ-Where's Min-ji?
вЂЄ-Hey, old man.

921
01:04:16,727 --> 01:04:17,854
вЂЄWhat do you think?

922
01:04:18,437 --> 01:04:19,313
вЂЄHuh?

923
01:04:19,397 --> 01:04:21,148
вЂЄIs it clocking to you that you're screwed?

924
01:04:25,361 --> 01:04:28,030
вЂЄWho the hell do you think you are?

925
01:04:28,114 --> 01:04:29,073
вЂЄYou think you're special?

926
01:04:29,156 --> 01:04:31,951
вЂЄShow me, then.
вЂЄTake off your clothes and fight.

927
01:04:32,034 --> 01:04:33,703
вЂЄWant me to take it off for you?

928
01:04:35,913 --> 01:04:36,914
<i>вЂЄLet me go!</i>

929
01:04:37,790 --> 01:04:39,458
вЂЄPut down the gun.

930
01:04:40,167 --> 01:04:41,669
вЂЄLet me go.

931
01:04:42,795 --> 01:04:44,714
вЂЄDischarge me right now!

932
01:04:50,928 --> 01:04:51,846
<i>вЂЄYou can't discharge him.</i>

933
01:04:51,929 --> 01:04:53,556
вЂЄYou know as well as I do, sir.

934
01:04:53,639 --> 01:04:56,475
вЂЄNo one can ever know he exists.

935
01:04:56,559 --> 01:04:58,352
<i>вЂЄCodename 66.</i>

936
01:04:58,436 --> 01:04:59,854
<i>вЂЄA North Korean operative who defected</i>

937
01:04:59,937 --> 01:05:01,814
<i>вЂЄand was recruited</i>
<i>вЂЄby South Korean intelligence.</i>

938
01:05:01,898 --> 01:05:03,566
<i>вЂЄHe acted as a double agent</i>
<i>вЂЄon five occasions</i>

939
01:05:03,649 --> 01:05:05,610
<i>вЂЄand has been credited with</i>
<i>вЂЄ17 infiltration missions in the North.</i>

940
01:05:05,693 --> 01:05:09,071
<i>вЂЄHe led the assassination operation</i>
<i>вЂЄtargeting North Korea's supreme commander,</i>

941
01:05:09,155 --> 01:05:12,325
<i>вЂЄprompting China and Russia</i>
<i>вЂЄto assign teams to track him.</i>

942
01:05:14,243 --> 01:05:15,119
вЂЄWhat the hell?

943
01:05:36,432 --> 01:05:38,768
<i>вЂЄDischarging someone like him</i>
<i>вЂЄis unthinkable.</i>

944
01:05:38,851 --> 01:05:41,646
вЂЄIf the North finds out he's still alive,

945
01:05:41,729 --> 01:05:43,356
вЂЄhis existence aloneвЂ¦

946
01:05:44,440 --> 01:05:45,858
вЂЄwill cause a diplomatic crisis.

947
01:05:52,782 --> 01:05:53,991
вЂЄTell me.

948
01:05:55,576 --> 01:05:56,577
вЂЄWhere's Min-ji?

949
01:06:37,868 --> 01:06:41,497
вЂЄAGENT KIM REACTIVATED

950
01:06:42,248 --> 01:06:43,624
{\an8}<i>вЂЄ-The law?</i>
<i>вЂЄ-Who the hell are you?</i>

951
01:06:44,834 --> 01:06:45,668
{\an8}<i>вЂЄI guessвЂ¦</i>

952
01:06:48,671 --> 01:06:50,339
{\an8}<i>вЂЄI'll just be a middle-aged outlaw.</i>

953
01:06:50,923 --> 01:06:53,342
{\an8}<i>вЂЄThe government denies</i>
<i>вЂЄAgent Kim's existence.</i>

954
01:06:53,426 --> 01:06:54,552
{\an8}<i>вЂЄArm the infiltration team.</i>

955
01:06:55,803 --> 01:06:56,846
{\an8}вЂЄHey, mister!

956
01:06:58,055 --> 01:07:00,266
{\an8}вЂЄIs that bastard sleeping right now?

957
01:07:00,349 --> 01:07:01,517
{\an8}<i>вЂЄIn this situation?</i>

958
01:07:02,059 --> 01:07:04,437
{\an8}вЂЄI'm only keeping you alive
вЂЄbecause I believe my daughter is.

959
01:07:07,148 --> 01:07:08,941
{\an8}<i>вЂЄ-Daddy!</i>
<i>вЂЄ-Is that you, Min-ji?</i>

960
01:07:10,818 --> 01:07:12,319
{\an8}<i>вЂЄI took care of the girl's body.</i>

961
01:07:14,864 --> 01:07:19,577
{\an8}вЂЄSubtitle translation by: Jenny Kim

